hm2NatMib.name: hm2NatMib

revisions.description: - Added missing protocol information - Changed stats to 64bit values
Removed all address types to be in sync with the FW MIB. The address type is now determined by the parser automatically.
- Added commit and pending actions variables - Added interface mapping tables - Use HmActionValue instead of TruthValue

hm2NatMib.contactinfo: Postal: Stuttgarter Str. 45-51 72654 Neckartenzlingen Germany Phone: +49 - 7127 -14 -0 E-mail: hac.support@belden.com
hm2NatMib.description: This MIB defines the SNMP interface for Hirschmann DNAT/SNAT/ Double NAT/1:1 NAT implementations Copyright (C)

hm2DnatMaxRules.name: hm2DnatMaxRules
hm2DnatMaxRules.description: Maximum number of allowed rules for DNAT.

hm2DoubleNatMaxRules.name: hm2DoubleNatMaxRules
hm2DoubleNatMaxRules.description: Maximum number of allowed rules for Double NAT.

hm2NatResetStatistics.name: hm2NatResetStatistics
hm2NatResetStatistics.description: Setting this value to action(2) will reset the statistics of the whole NAT module. It will be set to noop(1) automatically after reset.

hm2DnatRuleAppliedTrap.name: hm2DnatRuleAppliedTrap
hm2DnatRuleAppliedTrap.description: A rule of DNAT was applied. The rule is identified by the given rule index of the rule table.

hm2DnatRuleAppliedAndLoggedTrap.name: hm2DnatRuleAppliedAndLoggedTrap
hm2DnatRuleAppliedAndLoggedTrap.description: A rule of DNAT was applied and logged according to the current logging mechanism. The rule is identified by the given rule index of the rule table.

hm2DnatIfMappingRuleCount.name: hm2DnatIfMappingRuleCount
hm2DnatIfMappingRuleCount.description: Number of current DNAT IF mapping entries.

hm2DnatRulePendingActions.name: hm2DnatRulePendingActions
hm2DnatRulePendingActions.description: This value describes, whether the DNAT rule table was modified but not yet written to the firewall implementation (set to true). After writing all modifications to the firewall, the value switches automatically back to false.

hm2DnatCommitPendingActions.name: hm2DnatCommitPendingActions
hm2DnatCommitPendingActions.description: Setting this value to action(2) writes not yet committed changes to the firewall (DNAT and Interface Mapping Table). After writing all modifications, the value switches automatically back to noop(1).

hm2DnatRuleTable.name: hm2DnatRuleTable
hm2DnatRuleTable.description: The list of DNAT rules for this firewall.

hm2DnatRuleIndex.name: hm2DnatRuleIndex
hm2DnatRuleIndex.description: Rule index of this DNAT rule.

hm2DnatSourceAddress.name: hm2DnatSourceAddress
hm2DnatSourceAddress.description: Source address of packets to be NATed. Can be: - Single address (a.b.c.d), - address range in CIDR notation (a.b.c.d/n) - the name of a Netobject ($NetobjectName) - 'any' for no filtering at all - a prepending '!' selects the complement set

hm2DnatSourcePort.name: hm2DnatSourcePort
hm2DnatSourcePort.description: The source port of the packet to reroute. Allowed formats are: - keyword 'any' for no filtering or a protocol without ports - single port ('10') - port range with first and last port separated by hyphen ('10-15') - comma separated list of ports ('1235,25,123') - combination of the points above ('10,25-30,125,1993') The number of named ports (1 for each individual port, 2 for port ranges) must not exceed 15.

hm2DnatTargetAddress.name: hm2DnatTargetAddress
hm2DnatTargetAddress.description: Destination address of packets to be NATed. Can be: - Single address (a.b.c.d), - address range in CIDR notation (a.b.c.d/n) - the name of a Netobject ($NetobjectName) - 'any' for no filtering at all - a prepending '!' selects the complement set

hm2DnatTargetPort.name: hm2DnatTargetPort
hm2DnatTargetPort.description: The target port of the packet to reroute. Allowed formats are: - keyword 'any' - single port ('10') - port range with first and last port separated by hyphen ('10-15') - comma separated list of ports ('1235,25,123') - combination of the points above ('10,25-30,125,1993') The number of named ports (1 for each individual port, 2 for port ranges) must not exceed 15.

hm2DnatNewTargetAddress.name: hm2DnatNewTargetAddress
hm2DnatNewTargetAddress.description: The IP address of the machine to reroute packets to. Must be a single IP address (a.b.c.d).

hm2DnatNewTargetPort.name: hm2DnatNewTargetPort
hm2DnatNewTargetPort.description: The port to reroute packets to. Must be a single port or 'any'.

hm2DnatProto.name: hm2DnatProto
hm2DnatProto.description: The IP protocol (RFC 791) for protocol-independent filtering. The following values are currently supported: o icmp(1): Internet Control Message Protocol (RFC 792) o igmp(2): Internet Group Management Protocol o ipip(3): IP in IP tunneling (RFC 1853) o tcp(4): Transmission Control Protocol (RFC 793) o udp(5): User Datagram Protocol (RFC 768) o esp(6): IPsec Encapsulated Security Payload (RFC 2406) o ah(7): IPsec Authentication Header (RFC 2402) o icmpv6(8): Internet Control Message Protocol for IPv6 o any(9): apply to all protocols

hm2DnatRuleParams.name: hm2DnatRuleParams
hm2DnatRuleParams.description: Additional parameters to this rule as string. Currently only the value 'none' is valid. Reserved for future use.

hm2DnatLog.name: hm2DnatLog
hm2DnatLog.description: Set to true if application of this rule shall be logged.

hm2DnatTrap.name: hm2DnatTrap
hm2DnatTrap.description: Set to true if application of this rule shall send a trap.

hm2DnatRowStatus.name: hm2DnatRowStatus
hm2DnatRowStatus.description: This is a standard row status value: - active(1): The rule is active. Note that until committed, the rule will not be applied. - notInService(2): The rule is inactive because of user action. - notReady(3):The rule is inactive because it has an incomplete configuration. - createAndGo(4): Create the rule with default parameters activated. - createAndWait(5): Create the rule inactive. - destroy(6): Delete the rule. You cannot delete a rule with interface mappings to it.

hm2DnatDescription.name: hm2DnatDescription
hm2DnatDescription.description: User defined textual description related to this rule.

hm2DnatRuleIfMappingEntry.description: Entry in rule interface mapping table.

hm2DnatIfmRuleIndex.name: hm2DnatIfmRuleIndex
hm2DnatIfmRuleIndex.description: The index of the DNAT rule this mapping entry is assigned to.

hm2DnatIfmDirection.name: hm2DnatIfmDirection
hm2DnatIfmDirection.description: For DNAT, this can only be set to ingress, which is the interface on which a packet that is to be forwarded will arrive.

hm2DnatIfmPriority.name: hm2DnatIfmPriority
hm2DnatIfmPriority.description: The priority is the sorting key for rules in the chain to this interface. They don't need to be unique per interface, but in that case, no clear order can be assumed. Priorities are processed in ascending order (0 highest priority).

hm2DnatIfmInterface.name: hm2DnatIfmInterface
hm2DnatIfmInterface.description: The interface this mapping entry is assigned to. This has to be either an hm2AgentSwitchIpInterfaceIfIndex or an hm2AgentSwitchIpVlanIfIndex. Note that for physical interfaces this only works if the corresponding hm2AgentSwitchIpInterfaceRoutingMode is set to enable.

hm2DnatIfmRowStatus.name: hm2DnatIfmRowStatus
hm2DnatIfmRowStatus.description: The RowStatus value for this entry with the usual meanings: - active(1): The interface mapping is in place - notInService(2): The interface mapping is not in place because the user said so - notReady(3): The interface mapping is not in place because the agent said so - createAndGo(4): Create this mapping with the default priority and activate it. - createAndWait(5): Create this mapping deactivated. - destroy(6): Destroy this interface mapping.
